===Etymology===
Hebrew '''Absalom''' or '''Avshalom''' (אַבְשָׁלוֹם "Father/Leader of/is peace", Standard Hebrew Avšalom, Tiberian Hebrew ʾAḇšālôm). From אָב (av = 'father') + שָׁלוֹם (shalom = 'peace'.

===Proper noun===
'''Absalom'''
# The third [[son]] of [[David]], king of [[Israel]]

